President Obama has nominated Willie R. Stafford to serve as the United States Marshal for the Middle District of North Carolina. Stafford currently works as a background investigator for the Greensboro, North Carolina police department and has dedicated his career to protecting the people of North Carolina. He has shown courage and a commitment to public service. Stafford previously served with the Greensboro Police Department for nearly three decades and retired as the Assistant Chief of Police for the Western Operations Bureau. He holds a Master's Degree in Public Affairs and a Bachelor's Degree in American History and Psychology from the University of North Carolina.